g.desc: Select the last element as PIVOT and assume the first element...
g.text: Select the last element as PIVOT and assume the first element in the array is an element larger than the pivot.Blue arrow – traversing pointer.Red arrow – the element “greater" than the pivot.Orange block – the pivot.If the element in the traversing pointer is less than the pivot, we swap it with the “greater” element and move the greater element pointer forward. This process ensures that the element that is larger than the pivot gets moved at the end and lesser elements moved to the left.
